(
<tableCitation id="C6FAE7B1FFC20A2274893A9FAE89FF05" box="[649,734,151,177]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Leg setation and solenidia of adult Pergalumna (Pergalumna) dedzaensis sp. nov., P. (P.) paratsavoensis sp. nov. and P. (P.) parafrater sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF078282FFCC0A2C76973A9FAE5CFF60" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" tableUuid="DF078282FFCC0A2C76973A9FAE5CFF60">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Famulus of tarsus I inserted between seta 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2272D13A9FA8A7FF05" box="[1233,1264,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">ft”</emphasis>
and solenidion ω 
<subScript id="17FCD04FFFC20A2276AA3AC5ACE5FF6F" attach="right" box="[170,178,205,219]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">2</subScript>
. Solenidion on tibia IV inserted in anterior part of the segment, but close to the middle.
</paragraph>
