<subSubSection id="C3628181FFC20A2276C73B9BAD2BFE65" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC7D20AFFC20A2276C73B9BAD2BFE65" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,718]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2276C73B9BAD19FE19" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC20A2274333B9BAEFFFE19" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Starý" authorityYear="2022" box="[563,680,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parafrater">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2274333B9BAEFFFE19" box="[563,680,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">parafrater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the similarity between the new species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC20A2273133B9BAD2FFE65" authority="Balogh, 1960" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1960" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frater">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2273133B9BAC80FE65" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Pergalumna frater</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC20A2276DE3BBFAD2FFE65" author="Balogh, J." box="[222,376,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" pagination="15 - 40" refId="ref12985" refString="Balogh, J. (1960) Oribates (Acari) nouveaux d'Angola et du Congo Belge (2 eme serie). Companhia de Diamantes de Angola, Lisboa, 51, 15 - 40." type="journal article" year="1960">Balogh, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3628181FFC20A2276C73BD3A83BFD79" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC7D20AFFC20A2276C73BD3A83BFD79" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,718]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2276C73BD3AD6CFE41" bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC20A2277423BD3AE1FFE41" authority="Ermilov &amp; Starý, 2022" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Starý" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,584,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parafrater" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2277423BD3AE1FFE41" box="[322,584,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Pergalumna parafrater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A22744F3BD3AEFEFE41" bold="true" box="[591,681,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FB363FFC20A22744F3BD3AEFEFE41" box="[591,681,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC20A22723B3BD3A962FE41" authority="Balogh, 1960" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1960" box="[1083,1333,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frater">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A22723B3BD3A8C0FE41" box="[1083,1175,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">P. frater</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC20A22729E3BD3A962FE41" author="Balogh, J." box="[1182,1333,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" pagination="15 - 40" refId="ref12985" refString="Balogh, J. (1960) Oribates (Acari) nouveaux d'Angola et du Congo Belge (2 eme serie). Companhia de Diamantes de Angola, Lisboa, 51, 15 - 40." type="journal article" year="1960">Balogh, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Afrotropical region and 
<collectingCountry id="F36F929AFFC20A2277AB3BF7ADBCFDAD" box="[427,491,511,537]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Japan</collectingCountry>
in the absence of dorsosejugal suture and in the presence of median pore, setiform bothridial seta, three pairs of oval notogastral porose areas (
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A22753D382BAF0BFD89" box="[829,860,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">Aa</emphasis>
located between 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A227222382BA86FFD89" box="[1058,1080,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">la</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A227270382BA8DBFD89" box="[1136,1164,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">lm</emphasis>
, nearer to 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A227306382BA975FD89" box="[1286,1314,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">lm</emphasis>
), and long interlamellar seta. However, the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC20A227538384FAFC0FDD5" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1960" box="[824,919,583,609]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frater">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A227538384FAFC0FDD5" box="[824,919,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">P. frater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger body length (962–1062 versus 465–510), large notogastral porose areas (versus small), similar length of rostral, lamellar and interlamellar setae (versus 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2276EF3887AD54FD1D" box="[239,259,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">le</emphasis>
longer than 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A22778E3887ADF1FD1C" box="[398,422,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">ro</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC20A2277DC3887ADA5FD1C" box="[476,498,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="236">in</emphasis>
), the inverse oblique (versus parallel) localization of adanal lyrifissure to anal plate, and the presence (versus absence) of short rugoa and elongate tubercles on pteromorph.
</paragraph>
